	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Pretoria - The Gautrain service was suspended between Pretoria and Hatfield on Thursday due to a "minor derailment", the rail operator said. The derailment occurred as the train was approaching the Hatfield station at low speed around 08:30, Gautrain spokesperson Kesagee Nayager said. READ: Gautrain train service between PTA and Hatfield suspended "All passengers on board the train were safely evacuated without any injury and a full investigation is underway to determine the cause of the incident. Our technicians are also working to fully restore the service," Nayager said. A Gautrain bus service was transporting passengers between the two stations. The service to all other Gautrain stations remained unaffected.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  